    public static enum OSI.SystemProperty
extends Enum<OSI.SystemProperty>
    SystemProperty defines system properties used by OSI.

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • LOGBACK_CONFIGURATION_FILE

        public static final OSI.SystemProperty LOGBACK_CONFIGURATION_FILE
        Sets the logback configuration resource, rarely changed except for testing. Default is "osi-logback.xml".

        Note this is defined by logback. Although looked for on the classpath, logback names this "configurationFile".

        See Also:
        OSI.enable()

      • LOGBACK_CONTEXT_NAME

        public static final OSI.SystemProperty LOGBACK_CONTEXT_NAME
        Sets the logback context name, equivalently, a short tag identifying the application. Default is "default".

        Use this to distinguish merging of logging from multiple application.

        See Also:
        Setting the context name

      • LOGBACK_PROPERTIES_RESOURCE

        public static final OSI.SystemProperty LOGBACK_PROPERTIES_RESOURCE
        As an alternative to setting system properties, put properties here. Default is "osi-logback.properties" in the classpath root.

        These cannot, however, override these system properties which are used before the properties resource is loaded:

        • logback.configurationFile
        • logback.propertiesResource
        • logback.debug

      • LOGBACK_STYLES_RESOURCE

        public static final OSI.SystemProperty LOGBACK_STYLES_RESOURCE
        Sets a custom style file for logging, rarely changed. Default is "osi-logback-style.properties".
        See Also:
        LOGBACK_STYLES_RESOURCE

      • LOGBACK_STYLE

        public static final OSI.SystemProperty LOGBACK_STYLE
        Sets the default logging style. Default is "standard".

        See osi-logback-styles.properties for help and details.

        See Also:
        LOGBACK_STYLES_RESOURCE

      • LOGBACK_INCLUDED_RESOURCE

        public static final OSI.SystemProperty LOGBACK_INCLUDED_RESOURCE
        Sets the resource for additional included logging directives. Default is "osi-logback-included.xml".

        This is often changed (or one named osi-logback-included.xml is provided in the application class path) to control logging such as changing log levels.

        See Also:
        LOGBACK_INCLUDED_RESOURCE

      • LOGBACK_JMX

        public static final OSI.SystemProperty LOGBACK_JMX
        Enables JMX support for logback. Default is "true".

      • LOGBACK_DEBUG

        public static final OSI.SystemProperty LOGBACK_DEBUG
        Enables logback debugging. Default is "false".

        Enabling logback debugging sets log.level to "DEBUG".

        See Also:
        LOG_LEVEL

      • LOG_LEVEL

        public static final OSI.SystemProperty LOG_LEVEL
        Adjusts the general logging level when no more specific level is configured for a logger. Default is "WARN".
        See Also:
        Level

      • LOGBACK_ROOT_APPENDER

        public static final OSI.SystemProperty LOGBACK_ROOT_APPENDER
        Sets the root appender. Default is "console".

        Use in combination with a custom appender defined in osi-logback-included.xml.

        See Also:
        LOGBACK_INCLUDED_RESOURCE

      • LOGBACK_JANSI

        public static final OSI.SystemProperty LOGBACK_JANSI
        Enables ANSI color codes for logging, including Windows. Default is "false".
